<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Manifest1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Manifest,</orth> adj. 1) obvious, evident, not doubtful: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.358" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 358</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.172" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 92</bibl>.<lb />2) plain, open, notorious, public: <cit><quote>to retort your m. appeal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.303" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 303</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his reading and m. experience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.229" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 229</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>make't m. where she has lived,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 114</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you are m. house-keepers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.3.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 3, 54</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>